description:
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England are looking for enthusiastic and innovative GP educators to join the East of England School of Primary Care as a Training Programme Director.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will be responsible for coordinating and monitoring the Quality and Differential Attainment activities within their STP area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will support the Primary Care School in all aspects of East of England Primary Care workforce development, including finding innovative workforce solutions and advising on the commissioning of education for primary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve close liaison and negotiation with Training Hubs, NHS Trusts, NHS England and Area Teams, Universities, Royal Colleges, private sector and other health care providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a newly created post that will support the Primary Care School and Training Hubs in delivering key primary care workforce objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is one 2 PA role available covering the following STP area:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Suffolk and North East Essex&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will work with the Lead AD, Local TPDs, Training Hubs and local admins collaboratively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is paid at the GP00 pay-scale for the first year.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you like what you have read and think you have the skills and experience we need then don&#39;t delay, apply today! We get lots of applications for our roles and so we sometimes have to close our posts early. Don&#39;t miss out! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Janet Rutherford&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Primary Care Dean&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Janet.rutherford@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
